****************************

We are excited to announce the launch of a new service for supporting your US Custom Support Agreements (CSA).  Our goal in launching this new service is to assist sellers and TAMs through the CSA process giving you time back to focus on your customers. 

Please submit your CSA requests to ServiceCenter [mailto:servicecenter@microsoft.com]including the following information:

1.    Customer Name

2.    CSA Type including year

3.    Number of devices and migration – this could be the customer email forwarded or attached to your request

4.    Link to previous deal if the request is for a renewal (not required)

All requests will be completed during business hours (8am-5pm Central Time).

What's in scope:

·         New Renewal and Quarterly True Down

    For Global CSAs we will fulfill the US CSA deal only

·         Proposal – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Submit and update Enrollment form

·         Create CompassOne Deal

·         Draft contract – provided to the Requestor for review 

·         See CompassOne Deal through approvals

·         Ready for Signature contract – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Once PO & signed contract is received we will submit and see through processing

What's out of scope:

·         Extended Hotfix requests

·         Global CSA with multiple locations

·         Subject matter expertise regarding CSA specific questions prior to the Proposal or during Proposal phase 

o    Customer questions of this nature can be found on Premier Portal or by sending email to CSA Ops alias.

Special thank you to our pilot participants who have been gracious and patient while we prepare for launch!

3.    Number of devices and migration – this could be the customer email forwarded or attached to your request

4.    Link to previous deal if the request is for a renewal (not required)

All requests will be completed during business hours (8am-5pm Central Time).

What's in scope:

·         New Renewal and Quarterly True Down

      For Global CSAs we will fulfill the US CSA deal only
·         Proposal – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Submit and update Enrollment form

·         Create CompassOne Deal

·         Draft contract – provided to the Requestor for review 

·         See CompassOne Deal through approvals

·         Ready for Signature contract – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Once PO & signed contract is received we will submit and see through processing

What's out of scope:

·         Extended Hotfix requests

·         Global CSA with multiple locations

·         Subject matter expertise regarding CSA specific questions prior to the Proposal or during Proposal phase 

o    Customer questions of this nature can be found on Premier Portal or by sending email to CSA Ops alias.

Special thank you to our pilot participants who have been gracious and patient while we prepare for launch!

Please submit your CSA requests to ServiceCenter [mailto:servicecenter@microsoft.com]including the following information:

1.    Customer Name

2.    CSA Type including year

3.    Number of devices and migration – this could be the customer email forwarded or attached to your request

4.    Link to previous deal if the request is for a renewal (not required)

All requests will be completed during business hours (8am-5pm Central Time).

What's in scope:

·         New, Renewal and Quarterly True Down

    For Global CSAs, we will fulfill the US CSA deal only

·         Proposal – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Submit and update Enrollment form

·         Create CompassOne Deal

·         Draft contract – provided to the Requestor for review 

·         See CompassOne Deal through approvals

·         Ready for Signature contract – provided to the Requestor or directly to customer (whichever you prefer)

·         Once PO & signed contract is received, we will submit and see through processing

What's out of scope:

·         Extended Hotfix requests

·         Global CSA with multiple locations

·         Subject matter expertise regarding CSA specific questions prior to the Proposal or during Proposal phase 

o    Customer questions of this nature can be found on Premier Portal or by sending email to CSA Ops alias.
